{"name":"TextCtrl","description":"Use this control to display text, this text is not connected to any pins.\nYou can get the jquery object by calling getElement() and add your css styles to the text.\n\n","code":"/*\r\nUse this control to display the value of a pin\r\nThe value will be displayed as a text.\r\n*/\r\nvar ClassTextCtrlCount=0;\r\nclass TextCtrl extends ControlElement {\r\n\t    constructor(left, top, displayText){\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tsuper('text-ctrl', ClassTextCtrlCount++, left, top);\r\n\t\tthis.setValue(displayText);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tgetElement(){ return $('#' + super.getId() + '> p');}\t\r\n\tscale(value){\r\n\t\tsuper.scale(this.getElement(), value);\r\n\t}\r\n\trotate(degrees){\r\n\t\tsuper.rotate(this.getElement(), degrees);\r\n\t}\r\n\t\r\n\t//if bActivate == false then the pin gecomes grayed show that it is inactivated\r\n\tactive(bActivate){\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tif (bActivate === true){\r\n\t\t\tthis.getElement().css({color:'#000000'});\r\n\t\t\treturn;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tthis.getElement().css({color:'#cccccc'});\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tsetValue(value){\r\n\t\t//this.getElement().css({color:'#000000'});\r\n\t\tthis.value = value;\r\n\t\tthis.getElement().text(this.value);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n}//class\r\n\r\n","helpurl":"/controls/help/ctrl/TextCtrl","template":"<div id=\"text-ctrl\" class=\"text-ctrl\" style=\"position:absolute\">\r\n\t<p style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px\"></p>\r\n</div>"}